   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Hover over the <uicontrol>Playbook</uicontrol> tab and select <uicontrol>Clauses</uicontrol> to display a list of clauses in your library.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Scroll to the place in your document where you want to insert the clause. Place your cursor at the point of insertion.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="434"
                         href="../attachments/45220128/49676323.png"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click the <image placement="inline"
                      width="20"
                      href="../attachments/45220128/49676324.png"
                      id="image_apr_3gq_12c"/>
               <uicontrol>Insert Clause</uicontrol> icon to insert the clause into your
               document.</p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <image height="250"
                         placement="break"
                         width="648"
                         href="../attachments/45220128/49676325.png"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <div>
         <p>The inserted clause is automatically marked as a smart clause (shown with a grey
            border). You can go to <menucascade>
               <uicontrol>Document </uicontrol>
               <uicontrol> Clauses</uicontrol>
            </menucascade> in the X-Author pane to confirm the clause is now recognized in the
            document. If you decide you want to remove clause properties and revert the clause to
            static text, use the Document panel to <xref href="../working_with_clauses_4522_45220112/to_unmark_a_clause.xml#t298ED1A-BDF2-11F0-1430-09173F13E4C5">unmark the clause</xref>. When you check in the document, any smart clauses can be
            reconciled to the agreement and information for the inserted clause is added to the
            Agreement Clause related list on the agreement record.</p>
         <p>To learn how the Agreement Clause related list is populated with each insert, modify and
            delete action, refer to <xref href="../tracking_clauses_in_your__45220100/45220100.xml" format="dita"/>.</p>
         <note type="warning">
            <p>At this time, clauses can only be inserted in documents with "Full Access" protection.</p>
         </note>
      </div>
   </body>
